Your error comes from two issues: you replaced the DataFrame with the z-score array, and youâ€™re using a column name that doesnâ€™t exist in that DF. Use a separate variable for the z-scores and the actual column name (in your screenshot itâ€™s Income, not LoanAmount).

Hereâ€™s the correct, minimal z-score outlier filter:

from scipy.stats import zscore

df_z = loan_df.copy()
col = 'Income'  # change to 'LoanAmount' if that's the real column

z = zscore(df_z[col].astype(float), nan_policy='omit')
df_z = df_z.loc[(abs(z) < 3) | df_z[col].isna()]

df_z.head()

(If you want the plot after filtering:)

ax = df_z[col].hist(bins=20, figsize=(12,4))



